title: Tesla Earnings Live: 23rd October, 2019
bodyHTML:
11:14 pm
JP11:15pm

Hello everyone.

JP11:16pm

From the city of lights, NYC.

JP11:17pm

Where the weather...seems...welll..

11:17 pm
JR11:17pm

Hello!

JP11:17pm

Oh hello Joe!

JR11:17pm

It's gorgeous what are you talking about

11:17 pm
JP11:17pm

Well, here it is.

JP11:17pm

JP11:18pm

Up 20.30% per cent after a yuuuuuge beat.

11:18 pm
JP11:18pm

(That's Tesla, in case you hadn't guessed.)

JP11:19pm

Squeezeeeee.

JR11:19pm

Note short interest declined from a high of around 44m shares in May to 36m or so today.

11:19 pm
JP11:19pm

Rolling off a touch then.

JR11:19pm

Those few that got out earlier can feel (a little) better

JP11:19pm

Yes. A little.

11:19 pm
JP11:20pm

So what are the numbers looking like?

JR11:20pm

Shall we start with EPS?

JP11:20pm

Oh go on then.

11:20 pm
JP11:21pm

(For those listening at home, you can tune in here: https://edge.media...om/mmc/p/z7r768gm)

JR11:21pm

$1.91 per share, well above analyst expectations

JP11:21pm

That's the adjusted number.

11:21 pm
JR11:21pm

Yep

JP11:21pm

But the GAAP number was equally as good, $0.80 versus negative $1.37.

JR11:22pm

What about revenue growth?

11:22 pm
JP11:22pm

Well, this is where it gets interesting.

JP11:22pm

Rev growth was down 7 or so per cent.

JR11:22pm

Right...

11:22 pm
JP11:22pm

So cost control really kicked in this quarter, particularly versus the last.

JR11:23pm

That seems to be the key takeaway

JP11:23pm

Auto gross margin improved quarter on quarter from 18.9 per cent to 22.8 per cent.

11:24 pm
JR11:24pm

What does that mean?

JP11:24pm

It means they made cars much betterer.

JP11:25pm

Similarly operating expenses fell by $158m, and other income improved by $126m.

11:24 pm
JP11:25pm

The devil is in the details, however:

JP11:25pm

GAAP Automotive gross margin improved by 393bp QoQ to 22.8% (improved by 366bp QoQ excluding regulatory credits). Margin was impacted in part due to fundamental improvements in our operating efficiency, including higher fixed cost absorption, reductions in manufacturing and material costs and continued improvements in vehicle quality and in part due to Smart Summon-related deferred revenue recognition, FX and other non-recurring items. Improved gross profit combined with a decline in operating expenses resulted in material improvement of GAAP net income

JP11:25pm

Hmmm. I wonder what those non-recurring items are.

11:25 pm
JP11:25pm

Hope one of the analysts asks on the call (eta 5 mins).

JP11:26pm

How did the bonds look today Joe?

JR11:26pm

Unsurprisingly, the bonds rose after the announcement.

11:26 pm
JP11:26pm

Cos we know fixed income investors are so much smarter. That's why they bid up WeWork's debt to above par.

JR11:26pm

(so everyone is aware, my day job is covering debt markets)

JR11:27pm

Tesla's 2025 bonds up above 92 cents on the dollar

11:26 pm
JP11:27pm

(yeah, we might end up talking about repo if Elon bores us.)

JR11:27pm

Which may not sound great

JR11:27pm

BUT that's from below 82 cents on the dollar in May

11:27 pm
JP11:27pm

Ooof, a big jump.

JR11:28pm

Another interesting thing in the letter too

JP11:28pm

Go on Joe...

11:28 pm
JR11:29pm

Positive quarterly free cash flow going forward, with possible temporary exceptions, particularly around the launch and ramp of new products. We continue to believe our business has grown to the point of being self funding.”

JP11:29pm

Ah yes, temporary exceptions.

JP11:29pm

That old chestnut.

11:29 pm
JR11:29pm

Grown to the point of self funding... in case anyone was wondering if Tesla will be tapping bond markets soon.

JR11:29pm

But as you said, Jamie. With possible exceptions.

JP11:29pm

The green bond markets obvs.

11:29 pm
JP11:30pm

Get in that sweet ESG bracket for more bids.

JR11:30pm

If an oil tanker can issue a green bond, then anyone can.

JP11:30pm

Teeth smileTeeth smileTeeth smile

11:30 pm
JP11:30pm

To be fair though, free cash flow was really good -- $371m this quarter. Although payables were stretched $633m.

JP11:30pm

CONFERENCE CALL BEGINS.

JP11:30pm

Or is scheduled.

11:30 pm
JR11:31pm

Ah, I was enjoying the music

JP11:31pm

Same.

JR11:31pm

It's back!

11:31 pm
JP11:32pm

A quick thing before we begin.

JP11:32pm

Ex energy credits, auto gross profits (what a car makes before operating costs) was up $72m.

JP11:32pm

But they only delivered 1,830 more cars.

11:32 pm
JP11:32pm

I make that around $39,344 per car.

JR11:32pm

Hmmm...

JR11:32pm

That's a lot.

11:32 pm
JP11:32pm

The average selling price is around $55,000.

JP11:33pm

Or so I've read.

JR11:33pm

They made a big deal about cost savings and the idea that making more cars means fixed costs per car go down, but still, that's a lot.

11:33 pm
JP11:33pm

Yeah...huge quarter on quarter jump.

JR11:33pm

Any theories as to why?

JR11:34pm

Call is starting

11:33 pm
JP11:34pm

Hmm. Revenue recognition from full self driving tech will have higher gross margins, but otherwise a bit stumped.

JP11:34pm

OK HERE WE GO.

JP11:35pm

Elon to speak.

11:35 pm
JP11:35pm

He sounds chuffed.

JR11:35pm

"incredible quarter"

JP11:35pm

Great quarter guys.

11:35 pm
JP11:35pm

Shanghai chat -- this is the Chinese auto factory.

JR11:35pm

Cost reduction is his first point out of the gate

JP11:36pm

Hope the paint work is better than it is at the moment:

11:36 pm
JP11:36pm

JP11:36pm

Notice the blue engines.

JP11:36pm

Woah, weird stumble.

11:36 pm
JP11:37pm

It's odd how you expect Elon to sound like Tony Stark, but he's more like a first time BBC Newsnight guest speaking to Paxo.

JR11:37pm

Certainly sounds nervy

JP11:38pm

Oh yes, games on the screen in the car!

11:37 pm
JP11:38pm

That's what everyone wants when they're driving.

JR11:38pm

Thinks the model Y will outsell S,X and 3 combined.

JP11:38pm

Yeah that is very punchy.

11:38 pm
JR11:38pm

What do you make of Smart Summon, Jamie?

JP11:38pm

The Y is a cross-over, think a 7 seat Model 3 that looks a lot like a Model 3.

JP11:39pm

Hmmm no idea, it seems they rushed it out given all the videos.

11:39 pm
JP11:39pm

Woah, FULL SELF DRIVING THIS YEAR.

JR11:39pm

Maybe, said it will be "tight"

JP11:40pm

Yeah, but seems confident.

11:40 pm
JP11:40pm

That was the timeline from before.

JR11:40pm

Agreed. Followed up with: gigafactory will triple output over time.

JP11:40pm

Omg smile

11:41 pm
JP11:41pm

I'm trying to figure out how the China factory is on the balance sheet, as CapEx has been so low this year.

JP11:41pm

It's not wholly-owned, from what I can tell.

JP11:42pm

And here's CFO Zach Kirkhorn

11:42 pm
JP11:42pm

Lots of efficiency gains, labour hours per car down.

JP11:43pm

There we go, $30m of deferred revenue.

JR11:43pm

from smart summon

11:43 pm
JR11:43pm

yes

JP11:43pm

Yep.

JP11:43pm

Other income from a weakening dollar.

11:44 pm
JP11:44pm

Leasing had neg impact on FCF.

JR11:44pm

Makes sense

JR11:45pm

Isn't the dollar up a lot (to 3q) this year?

11:45 pm
JR11:45pm

Dollar has weakened this month

JP11:45pm

Hmmm.

JP11:45pm

And foreign mix is up.

11:47 pm
JR11:47pm

Tesla's strategy to become a giant distributed global utility. Can't fault ambition.

JR11:47pm

Discussion has turned to solar.

JP11:47pm

All about the total addressable market baby.

11:47 pm
JP11:47pm

Btw here's the dollar chart:

JP11:47pm

JP11:48pm

So weakened at the end of the month.

11:49 pm
JP11:49pm

Wait no. That's last three months. Was strong.

JR11:50pm

Strengthen to Sept 30 and then has fallen this month. but ytd to Sept 30 the dollar was up 3.3 per cent according to DXY index. Anyway, let's move on.

JP11:50pm

Yep interesting.

11:50 pm
JP11:50pm

Elon intervening a lot here with the solar stuff.

JR11:51pm

He has certainly perked up a bit.

JP11:51pm

By the way, solar doesn't work in a power cut. Been a big issue in California recently. http://www.capradi...outages-heres-why/

11:51 pm
JP11:52pm

Powerwalls will though.

JR11:52pm

Given the strength of Tesla's earnings they have spent a long time discussing single-visit install of solar in a home.

JP11:53pm

Ok questions!

11:53 pm
JR11:53pm

First question about word of mouth versus advertising

JR11:53pm

We have no plans to advertise at this time

JP11:54pm

Yeah, seems content with straight demand.

11:53 pm
JR11:54pm

Twitter is enough probably

JP11:54pm

hah yes.

JP11:54pm

Will use advertising to educate customers though.

11:54 pm
JP11:54pm

Wait. Wait.

JP11:54pm

CensoredCensoredCensored

JP11:54pm

The questions are not being asked by analysts.

11:54 pm
JP11:54pm

This is the first time!

JP11:55pm

Were they prepared? Normally the Street asks after seeing the results.

JR11:55pm

Yeah, they are being read out as either institutional or retail questions

11:55 pm
JP11:55pm

That is odd.

JP11:56pm

Not quite the pre-recorded Netflix bad, but a change which is definitely less transparent.

JP11:56pm

Elon: Solar as big as the cars.

11:57 pm
JR11:57pm

Very odd.

JP11:57pm

It's worth pointing out that if demand is higher than supply for the future, and no advertising needed.

JR11:58pm

(RE questions being read out)

11:57 pm
JP11:58pm

But your revenues fell year on year, while capacity increased.

JP11:58pm

Then there is a demand issue.

JP11:59pm

No questions on the financials yet.

11:59 pm
JR11:59pm

Expect to have the basic functionality of a robo taxi by the end of this year

JP12:00am

Still on robotaxis -- "from car to robotaxi, the biggest step change in asset value in history by far".

JP12:00am

RocketRocketRocket

12:00 am
JP12:00am

Vix-mageddon, eat yr heart out.

JR12:00am

Yeah, for the full capability expected end of next year. That's what he said right?

JR12:00am

Wait and see

12:00 am
JP12:00am

OK. Here are where questions are submitted:

JP12:00am

https://www.say.com/qa/tesla

JP12:01am

With just first name and initial.

12:01 am
JR12:01am

Any they go through in order or get chosen?

JP12:01am

Chosen.

JP12:02am

And there's upvoting on questions!

12:02 am
JR12:02am

Haha.

JR12:02am

This is the last question from institutional investors.

JP12:02am

Question from an "institutional investor" on Full Self Driving pricing,

12:02 am
JR12:03am

Such a grilling on the financials then. Really dug in. I feel so much better informed.

JP12:03am

Yeah man wow!

JR12:03am

Onto retail investor questions

12:03 am
JR12:03am

Another question about auto stopping at traffic lights.

JP12:04am

So far robotaxis, solar, full self driving pricing and advertising.

JP12:04am

And now Model Y.

12:04 am
JP12:05am

Ramping...popular word in Tesla bingo.

JP12:05am

Oooh. Tesla insurance.

JP12:06am

Freudian slip from Zach? Lost versus launched.

12:06 am
JR12:06am

He seems happy with how it is going.

JR12:06am

Only in California right now

JP12:06am

Yep, although when it launched it seemed to be a lot more expensive than the normal providers.

12:06 am
JP12:06am

From feedback online.

JR12:07am

Few specifics. It's been "well received," said Zach.

JP12:07am

Last question.

12:08 am
JP12:08am

Skepticism over self-driving, and how is it going to work?

JP12:08am

Supervised to start.

JP12:09am

Three levels: 1. autonomous but needs supervision (feature complete) 2. Safe enough to drive with no supervision 3. Regulators convinced.

12:09 am
JR12:09am

Regulators need to be convinced. That's the final hurdle said Mr Musk.

JR12:09am

Ahhhhhh, here we go.

JP12:09am

Ahh here are the analysts!

12:09 am
JR12:09am

Phew.

JR12:09am

I'll take off my coat

JP12:10am

ha.

12:10 am
JP12:10am

China headwinds to start, some issues in Q4 but hard to forecast with the factory ramp up.

JP12:11am

S+X margins improved quarter on quarter.

JP12:11am

Every line item, become a lot more focused in terms of costs.

12:12 am
JP12:12am

Non-recurring items....Smart Summon is debatable as to non-recurring.

JR12:12am

Back on FX. Since they don't hedge it has an impact. They will see how this quarter plays out.

JP12:12am

Weird given the dollar move.

12:12 am
JR12:13am

Right

JP12:13am

HERE'S JONAS, or his surrogate.

JR12:13am

Reiterating that they needs to get costs down in the new China factory.

12:13 am
JP12:14am

Yep, and optimising at Fremont.

JP12:14am

Question about selling batteries to other car companies.

JR12:15am

They're open to it

12:15 am
JR12:15am

to sum up

JP12:15am

Yep.

JP12:16am

Macquarie analyst wants to know how software could be monetised.

12:16 am
JR12:16am

The goal with the infotainment system is to say what is the most amount of fun you can have in a car

JP12:17am

Some cars are fun to drive, we should add.

JP12:17am

12:17 am
JR12:18am

Is that the model Y?

JP12:18am

I don't know but it looks fun.

JP12:18am

Question on tax credits, and what we can expect with tightening EU regs next year.

12:18 am
JP12:18am

We're not counting on it.

JP12:19am

Interesting they manage the business without the credits, given they've booked around half a billion of them over the past year.

JR12:20am

Indeed

YT I'm trying to look about development from the Walmart law suits, I can't find any accurate news - it's also hard to find those expenses on TSLA income statement or balance sheet as they're becoming cost efficient... Is anybody else wondering?
12:20 am
JP12:20am

What's the next question Joe?

JR12:21am

Elon thinks Tesla Cybertrack is their best product ever. Also a question on geographic mix of orders.

Jamie Powell (FT Alphaville) YT, you'll need to post twice in a normal post before we can see it.
JR12:22am

Sorry Semitruck

12:22 am
JP12:22am

Ha, no I misheard also.

JR12:22am

cybertrack is part of the infotainment system :/

JP12:22am

Teeth smile

12:23 am
JP12:23am

Next question from New Street research.

JR12:24am

On Model S and X

JP12:24am

Yep, it's two high end cars.

12:24 am
JP12:24am

Minor importance to the future.

JR12:25am

"They are niche products... we continue to make them more for sentimental reasons than anything else."

JP12:25am

Gosh, wonder what the current owners will make of that.

12:25 am
JP12:25am

Question from reader:

JP12:25am

I'm trying to look about development from the Walmart law suits, I can't find any accurate news - it's also hard to find those expenses on TSLA income statement or balance sheet as they're becoming cost efficient... Is anybody else wondering?

JP12:25am

Yep, can't see any expenses from these on going law suits about its solar roofs causing fires.

12:27 am
JP12:27am

Model X and Model S getting more orders this quarter than before.

JP12:27am

So not forgotten about -- new power improvement.

JR12:28am

Based on software updates.

12:28 am
JP12:28am

Yes, will push the range up.

JP12:28am

To high 370s or 380s. I think he said.

JR12:29am

I wish my phone battery would improve with software updates

12:29 am
JP12:29am

Did Elon just snigger then?

JR12:30am

Dan Levy at Credit Suisse up next.

JP12:30am

Question about the China ramp up after difficult period with the 3 ramp up.

12:31 am
JP12:31am

Elon seems to say -- I have no idea.

JR12:31am

Yeah, I feel like a lot of the answers have been pretty vague

JP12:31am

As smooth as the stock market. But no other car company has this problem of varying production once its in full output mode.

12:31 am
JP12:31am

It's basic stuff.

JP12:32am

Question on energy -- Elon thinks solar is the next big thing. Clear from the whole call tbh.

JP12:32am

You know, that business which has been commoditised by cheap panels from China.

12:32 am
JR12:32am

For sure! Will grow faster than automotive, he says.

JP12:33am

That's it.

JR12:33am

Yeah. What did you make of it?

12:33 am
JP12:33am

I don't know, I felt the analyst questions were a bit light. No asking about how all the improvements quarter on quarter were so massive.

JP12:34am

And, how the gross margin jumped so massively.

JR12:34am

Same. No drilling down on delivery expectations, how gross margin jumped so much, etc etc

12:34 am
JP12:34am

Guess we'll find out more when the 10Q files tomorrow or next week.

JP12:34am

Nothing on delivery logistics either.

JP12:34am

Anyway!

12:34 am
JR12:34am

Well, thanks for having me

JP12:35am

It's late-ish in New York and I need a drink.

JP12:35am

Thanks for coming Joe!

12:35 am
JR12:35am

That was fun!

JP12:35am

Markets Live will resume it's normal service tomorrow, 11am UK time.

JP12:35am

Until then.

12:35 am
JP12:35am

Good evening.

JR12:36am

Bye!
